items.title: The 12 unlikeliest MVP Award winners
items.summary: The Indians' Jose Ramirez has a shot at the American League MVP Award. And as surprising as that would be, it still would not rank among the dozen biggest MVP surprises in Major League history.
items.content: The Indians' Jose Ramirez has a shot at the American League MVP Award. And as surprising as that would be, it still would not rank among the dozen biggest MVP surprises in Major League history.

items.title: No two ways about it: Ohtani one of a kind
items.summary: What if the talents of both a top pitcher and a top hitter could somehow come in the form of one single player? How would it work? That's what teams considering bidding on Japanese phenom Shohei Ohtani are trying to figure out now that it seems certain he'll be posted this offseason.
items.content: What if the talents of both a top pitcher and a top hitter could somehow come in the form of one single player? How would it work? items.title: J.D.'s incredible season hidden in plain sight
items.summary: Maybe this statistic will blow you mind like it did mine: Giancarlo Stanton does not lead the Major Leagues in slugging percentage. Well, technically he does, because the two players ahead of him don't quite have the plate appearances to qualify.
